abstract: LONDON, Jan. 9. A Russian official telegram states that a Russian detachment, which had crossed the Balkans by by-ways, occupied on Tuesday a position in the rear of the Turkish fortifications in the Trojan pass. The Turks, being also attacked in front, abandoned their positions, which were occupied by the Russians, whose vanguard advanced in the direction of Teke. The Russian loss in these operations was unimportant.
